WEBVTT

00:02.921 --> 00:04.721
INTERVIEWER:
<i>We'll start in, what, 30 seconds?</i>

00:04.923 --> 00:06.925
<i>We good for 30? Thanks. Um...</i>

00:07.676 --> 00:09.594
<i>- So, uh...</i>
- STUDIO ENGINEER: <i>Move your lav up</i>

00:09.844 --> 00:10.929
<i>just a little bit for me,
if you could, please?</i>

00:11.179 --> 00:12.597
INTERVIEWER: <i>Move it up?</i>

00:14.516 --> 00:15.892
<i>Where is it?</i>

00:16.101 --> 00:17.227
<i>Oh, I got it.</i>

00:18.395 --> 00:20.605
<i>- Is that better?</i>
- STUDIO ENGINEER: <i>Thank you.</i>

00:20.855 --> 00:22.895
INTERVIEWER:
<i>Is... Is the sound for both of us good?</i>

00:22.941 --> 00:24.609
STUDIO ENGINEER: <i>It's good. Thank you.</i>
INTERVIEWER: <i>Okay.</i>

00:24.859 --> 00:27.237
<i>Right, well, um, when you're ready,
shall we start?</i>

00:27.445 --> 00:29.114
♪ (SOFT ROCK PLAYING) ♪

00:30.907 --> 00:32.116
<i>Jane, good morning.</i>

00:32.366 --> 00:33.910
Good morning.

00:36.621 --> 00:38.623
<i>Since your early days
as a political strategist,</i>

00:38.873 --> 00:41.292
<i>you've been known by a certain name,</i>

00:41.459 --> 00:42.627
<i>Calamity Jane.</i>

00:42.794 --> 00:45.380
JANE: <i>Yeah, I've, I've been called
a lot of names.</i>

00:45.588 --> 00:47.966
INTERVIEWER: <i>Did you ever work for
a politician you did not believe in?</i>

00:48.299 --> 00:51.619
JANE: <i>Oh, sure. I could, I could convince
myself of anything if the price was right.</i>

00:55.390 --> 00:57.934
PUNDIT 1: <i>There is no coming
back from a shot like that.</i>

00:58.143 --> 00:59.728
<i>She is on fire. I'll tell you,</i>

00:59.936 --> 01:02.230
<i>her opponents are scrambling
to keep up with her momentum.</i>

01:02.439 --> 01:03.732
INTERVIEWER: <i>How important is honesty?</i>

01:03.940 --> 01:05.650
Well, truth is relative in politics.

01:05.900 --> 01:08.111
The truth is what I tell
the electorate the truth is.

01:09.738 --> 01:11.406
REPORTER 1:
<i>In politics, money does talk,</i>

01:11.614 --> 01:12.907
<i>and it's about to do a lot more talking.</i>

01:13.116 --> 01:14.159
<i>The U.S. Supreme Court now</i>

01:14.409 --> 01:16.411
<i>has lifted limits
on campaign contributions,</i>

01:16.828 --> 01:19.330
<i>ushering in a new era of
unfettered political spending.</i>

01:19.622 --> 01:22.834
INTERVIEWER: <i>When you began your career,
you must've had heroes, role models?</i>

01:23.126 --> 01:24.502
Who are my heroes? (INHALES)

01:25.336 --> 01:27.172
Well, when I first started
in this business,

01:27.338 --> 01:29.841
my heroes were politicians and leaders,

01:30.925 --> 01:32.427
and then I met them.

01:32.635 --> 01:33.635
(JANE CHUCKLES)

01:33.678 --> 01:35.718
PUNDIT 2: <i>Look, the bottom line
is they have created</i>

01:35.764 --> 01:37.766
<i>an inherently corrupt system here.</i>

01:38.141 --> 01:40.661
PUNDIT 3: <i>We're talking about a woman
who is combative at heart.</i>

01:40.977 --> 01:42.520
<i>She's, uh...
She's belligerent, she's entitled,</i>

01:42.771 --> 01:44.814
<i>and when she doesn't get her way,
she makes noise.</i>

01:45.148 --> 01:47.150
PUNDIT 4: <i>She's a strategist
who can't be trusted.</i>

01:47.525 --> 01:49.027
<i>I say give her a glass of wine,</i>

01:49.194 --> 01:51.321
<i>and she might spill the truth for once.</i>

01:51.529 --> 01:54.324
INTERVIEWER: <i>You had some personal
missteps that became very public.</i>

01:54.783 --> 01:57.863
I mean, it's almost like car races.
No one watches a car race to see who wins.

01:58.328 --> 02:01.539
They watch the car race to see who wrecks,

02:02.707 --> 02:05.168
- who goes up in flames.
- (INTERVIEWER LAUGHS)

02:05.376 --> 02:07.045
REPORTER 2 <i>: ...in the wake
of serious political scandals.</i>

02:07.295 --> 02:09.464
PUNDIT 5: <i>She resigned on Monday
after they, uh, filed a criminal complaint</i>

02:09.672 --> 02:12.342
<i>accusing her of, get this,
violating election laws.</i>

02:12.550 --> 02:15.011
PUNDIT 6: <i>She's obviously
at the center of a firestorm</i>

02:15.220 --> 02:16.513
<i>and huge controversy.</i>

02:17.180 --> 02:19.182
INTERVIEWER: <i>No longer idealistic?</i>

02:19.516 --> 02:21.309
You know, you need to be idealistic

02:21.518 --> 02:24.229
to get into this thing,
to keep going, but...

02:25.021 --> 02:27.148
You know, once that is gone,

02:28.233 --> 02:31.027
there's... There's no getting that back.

02:32.070 --> 02:33.530
You know?

02:34.072 --> 02:36.825
No matter how hard you try. You can't.

02:42.664 --> 02:45.333
INTERVIEWER: <i>You stepped away from
your professional and political success</i>

02:45.542 --> 02:49.045
<i>for a fight that might not be
winnable in this lifetime.</i>

02:50.004 --> 02:51.673
<i>How did you get here?</i>

02:52.841 --> 02:54.217
<i>What happened?</i>

